1
00:00:02,302 --> 00:00:03,804
Four hundred matches, undefeated?

2
00:00:05,766 --> 00:00:07,980
In the world karate championships?

3
00:00:08,314 --> 00:00:11,988
I look forward to seeing
how far that record goes.

4
00:00:12,071 --> 00:00:13,532
Ah, no.

5
00:00:13,992 --> 00:00:17,373
Unfortunately, I couldn't take part
in the last tournament...

6
00:00:17,457 --> 00:00:19,294
so it went down as a forfeit loss.

7
00:00:19,377 --> 00:00:22,885
He skipped the tournament
to come see me, you know.

8
00:00:22,968 --> 00:00:25,473
Oh?
Ah, no...

9
00:00:25,556 --> 00:00:29,689
If not for that, the undefeated legend
would still be going strong.

10
00:00:29,773 --> 00:00:33,364
But in the Suzuki household,
brute force has no use.

11
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:39,292
Do you have what it takes
to one day carry...

12
00:00:39,376 --> 00:00:42,298
the entire Suzuki Group on your shoulders?
Huh?

13
00:00:43,008 --> 00:00:46,431
Now, now, Tomoko,
it's far too early for talk like that.

14
00:00:46,515 --> 00:00:49,187
The two of them are still in high school.

15
00:00:49,854 --> 00:00:53,487
No. Now that our eldest, Ayako...
- Suzuki Shiro (51), Sonoko's father (Chairman of the Suzuki Financial Group)
- Suzuki Tomoko (43), Sonoko's mother

16
00:00:53,570 --> 00:00:56,118
has been promised
in marriage to the Tomizawa family...

17
00:00:56,201 --> 00:00:59,124
the only path left
for an heir is to have...

18
00:00:59,207 --> 00:01:02,463
Sonoko's future husband
marry into our family.

19
00:01:02,839 --> 00:01:06,346
By rights, I had hoped
to weigh family standing and education...

20
00:01:06,430 --> 00:01:10,646
and select someone truly worthy
of the Suzuki household.

21
00:01:11,773 --> 00:01:15,197
And yet, you're seeing some drifter,
still just a high schooler...

22
00:01:15,281 --> 00:01:18,412
gallivanting off to study abroad
for "warrior's training"?

23
00:01:18,495 --> 00:01:20,708
What are you thinking, Sonoko?

24
00:01:20,791 --> 00:01:23,380
That's my business, isn't it?

25
00:01:24,340 --> 00:01:27,221
I have no intention
of inheriting this house anyway.

26
00:01:27,513 --> 00:01:29,100
Why, you...

27
00:01:29,559 --> 00:01:30,561
Now, now.

28
00:01:31,062 --> 00:01:34,819
Makoto-kun, it's about time
for your return flight.

29
00:01:34,904 --> 00:01:37,241
I'll have a car
take you to the airport.

30
00:01:37,325 --> 00:01:39,829
We'll continue this discussion
another time.

31
00:01:39,914 --> 00:01:41,625
Ah... yes.

32
00:01:42,585 --> 00:01:46,218
And once your next tournament
is decided, let me know.

33
00:01:46,301 --> 00:01:49,057
I may not look it,
but I'm a fan of martial arts.

34
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:50,142
Yes.

35
00:01:51,311 --> 00:01:53,190
(cell phone ringtone)
Hm?

36
00:01:55,152 --> 00:01:57,532
Oh, it's Ran calling.

37
00:01:58,075 --> 00:02:00,579
Hold on, I'm not finished talking...

38
00:02:00,956 --> 00:02:02,625
Hello?

39
00:02:03,627 --> 00:02:06,216
Huh? Kaito Kid?

40
00:02:06,383 --> 00:02:07,510
(News: Early this morning, a notice arrived for Suzuki Group advisor Jirokichi Suzuki...
Once again targeting a jewel belonging to advisor Jirokichi Suzuki... the alexandrite known
as the Green Emperor... will be stolen at 10 p.m., after the
first day of the exhibition closes. The Metropolitan Police will tighten
security around the Suzuki Grand Museum... while also accounting for the possibility
he disguises himself as a staff member... verifying identities swiftly...)

41
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:13,730
That's right, Kid... a heist notice from Kaito Kid has been delivered.

42
00:02:13,730 --> 00:02:17,613
It's all over the TV news right now, about the heist notice he sent.

43
00:02:17,697 --> 00:02:20,912
No way. Seriously? For real?

44
00:02:20,996 --> 00:02:24,043
Then I'll call Uncle Jirokichi right away.

45
00:02:24,127 --> 00:02:26,131
Ah, wait... (call disconnects)

46
00:02:26,798 --> 00:02:29,846
Honestly, Kyogoku-san is here today...

47
00:02:29,930 --> 00:02:33,020
I wanted to tell her not to get all
worked up like she always does.

48
00:02:33,478 --> 00:02:35,274
Backfired completely.

49
00:02:35,357 --> 00:02:39,032
(cell phone ringing)
Ah, hello? Uncle?

50
00:02:39,324 --> 00:02:42,956
I heard all about it.
Kid-sama's coming again, isn't he?

51
00:02:43,749 --> 00:02:45,252
"Kid-sama"...

52
00:02:48,091 --> 00:02:49,844
Sun blazing,
heat I won't lose to...

53
00:02:49,929 --> 00:02:51,514
a stylish, dashing
deduction show.

54
00:02:51,598 --> 00:02:55,564
A battle between the two men Sonoko adores?
Jirokichi's all-out ultimate weapon.

55
00:02:55,648 --> 00:02:56,943
Seeing through the one and only truth...

56
00:02:57,026 --> 00:02:58,695
Looks like a kid,
mind of an adult...

57
00:02:58,779 --> 00:03:01,493
His name is Detective Conan!

58
00:03:03,419 --> 00:03:08,764
♪~

59
00:04:36,898 --> 00:04:42,910
~♪

60
00:04:44,786 --> 00:04:50,086
"Thief Kid vs. Makoto Kyogoku (Part 1)".

61
00:04:51,635 --> 00:04:54,182
One... one hundred matches,
all losses?

62
00:04:54,851 --> 00:04:57,355
You're telling me
every one was breached?

63
00:04:57,857 --> 00:05:02,407
The state-of-the-art security system
we only just completed the other day?

64
00:05:02,490 --> 00:05:04,161
Y-yes.

65
00:05:04,244 --> 00:05:07,250
Of course, this is all
on the computer simulation.

66
00:05:07,459 --> 00:05:11,467
We input Kaito Kid's
behavioral patterns to date...

67
00:05:11,550 --> 00:05:13,471
and the results of the simulation...

68
00:05:13,554 --> 00:05:15,099
Th-they were...

69
00:05:15,183 --> 00:05:17,604
Ungh... hmm.

70
00:05:17,938 --> 00:05:21,445
What do we do?
The notice day is tomorrow.

71
00:05:21,863 --> 00:05:25,829
At this rate, we'll just hand it
right over to that scoundrel.

72
00:05:26,748 --> 00:05:30,713
The alexandrite I finally got my hands on...

73
00:05:30,881 --> 00:05:32,717
after scouring the entire globe...

74
00:05:33,177 --> 00:05:37,102
the verdant emperor,
the Green Emperor.

75
00:05:37,685 --> 00:05:42,362
B-but Kid's disguise skills
let him impersonate anyone...

76
00:05:42,445 --> 00:05:46,871
plus a mind that adapts to any situation
on the fly...

77
00:05:46,955 --> 00:05:49,794
and when you add in physical abilities...

78
00:05:49,877 --> 00:05:52,006
that seem barely human as data points...

79
00:05:52,090 --> 00:05:55,471
the result will be the same
no matter the security system.

80
00:05:55,555 --> 00:05:58,854
If anything, why not lower
Kid's numbers by twenty percent...

81
00:05:58,937 --> 00:06:01,818
and run the simulation again?

82
00:06:01,901 --> 00:06:05,533
He's human too. Surely he has days
when he's not feeling well.

83
00:06:05,616 --> 00:06:10,794
Fool. That man is a master thief
renowned for his swiftness.

84
00:06:10,878 --> 00:06:13,716
And he sharpens his skills
every single time.

85
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:16,388
Even a twenty percent increase
wouldn't be enough.

86
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:19,896
Well, a hundred matches,
all losses.

87
00:06:19,979 --> 00:06:23,737
Putting the gem on display knowing
it'll be taken hardly makes sense.

88
00:06:23,820 --> 00:06:27,535
It pains me, but this time
we'll just have to postpone the exhibit...

89
00:06:27,619 --> 00:06:29,372
Advisor Suzuki.
Hm?

90
00:06:29,749 --> 00:06:33,214
There's a... strange man
at the entrance just now...

91
00:06:33,505 --> 00:06:36,094
demanding to be let in to see you.
What?

92
00:06:36,178 --> 00:06:38,057
Gwaah!
Ugh!

93
00:06:51,291 --> 00:06:52,669
Haaah!

94
00:06:54,130 --> 00:06:55,258
Whoa!

95
00:06:58,097 --> 00:07:00,434
Haaah!

96
00:07:03,565 --> 00:07:05,486
Whoa, waah!

97
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:30,036
Any further sparring would be pointless.

98
00:07:30,411 --> 00:07:33,250
Ugh... ungh...

99
00:07:34,377 --> 00:07:39,679
I humbly request an audience
with advisor Jirokichi Suzuki.

100
00:07:39,764 --> 00:07:42,936
(panting)
What's all this?

101
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:45,274
A-advisor...

102
00:07:47,487 --> 00:07:50,659
My name is Makoto Kyogoku.
I'm a humble young man...

103
00:07:50,744 --> 00:07:53,917
who has the honor
of dating Sonoko-san.

104
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,590
Oho, oho, oho.
Sonoko's boyfriend.

105
00:07:58,092 --> 00:08:00,304
And what business
brings you here?

106
00:08:00,388 --> 00:08:02,683
I heard that you possess the gem...

107
00:08:02,768 --> 00:08:05,439
that this so-called kaito kid
is targeting.

108
00:08:05,816 --> 00:08:09,907
If so, I beg you...

109
00:08:10,157 --> 00:08:12,955
to allow me, Makoto Kyogoku,
a place among your guards.

110
00:08:13,372 --> 00:08:14,707
Denied.

111
00:08:15,334 --> 00:08:17,130
I-I implore you, reconsider.

112
00:08:18,632 --> 00:08:21,430
Hmm. So young.

113
00:08:21,973 --> 00:08:25,312
I take it you can't stomach
the fact that Sonoko...

114
00:08:25,396 --> 00:08:26,983
is so smitten with that scoundrel?

115
00:08:29,362 --> 00:08:33,370
But rest easy.
That's like a case of the measles.

116
00:08:33,454 --> 00:08:34,915
The... measles?

117
00:08:35,207 --> 00:08:38,255
Once I've captured that rogue...

118
00:08:38,338 --> 00:08:41,511
I'll make her forget him
clean and clear.

119
00:08:41,595 --> 00:08:43,515
Ah, advisor!

120
00:08:44,935 --> 00:08:48,358
Alright, out you go, out you go.
(cell phone ringtone)

121
00:08:49,319 --> 00:08:51,323
Ah, Sonoko? Perfect timing...

122
00:08:51,406 --> 00:08:54,747
Hey, by any chance,
has Makoto-san shown up there?

123
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,585
Advisor, please, let's talk...

124
00:08:58,253 --> 00:09:00,591
I'm at Haneda Airport right now...

125
00:09:01,092 --> 00:09:05,142
but while I was doing his check-in,
he just disappeared.

126
00:09:05,769 --> 00:09:09,818
Apparently he asked our driver
for your address, Uncle...

127
00:09:10,277 --> 00:09:13,116
so I thought maybe
he'd gone over to your place.

128
00:09:14,285 --> 00:09:19,420
What sort of man is he?
I hear he's a karateka.

129
00:09:19,504 --> 00:09:24,055
He's no ordinary karateka.
Four hundred matches in the world championships, undefeated.

130
00:09:24,138 --> 00:09:27,228
The unbeatable prince of kicks,
who has no equal anywhere.

131
00:09:28,689 --> 00:09:33,031
F-four hundred matches, undefeated?

132
00:09:34,827 --> 00:09:39,627
Huh? Keep security out
of the gem's exhibition room?

133
00:09:40,755 --> 00:09:45,639
Why on earth? Kaito Kid
is coming to steal it!

134
00:09:46,057 --> 00:09:49,355
Because it'd interfere with the latest
security system, apparently.

135
00:09:49,439 --> 00:09:52,612
Advisor Suzuki called me
about it just a moment ago.

136
00:09:52,988 --> 00:09:56,578
What's that old man
thinking this time?

137
00:09:56,661 --> 00:10:01,296
And this is the footage
he sent over after the call.

138
00:10:02,006 --> 00:10:05,512
Eh... footage?
Ungh...

139
00:10:06,389 --> 00:10:11,524
A single man,
surrounded by guys aiming pistols at him.

140
00:10:11,859 --> 00:10:17,244
The rounds are BBs, of course,
but at this range and with these numbers...

141
00:10:17,328 --> 00:10:19,707
and the man in the center...

142
00:10:19,792 --> 00:10:23,883
is wearing a gas mask
that blocks his vision.

143
00:10:24,425 --> 00:10:26,889
You'd think there's no way
he could dodge it all, right?

144
00:10:34,070 --> 00:10:37,118
Come at me like you mean
to take me down, all at once, please.

145
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:42,211
(gunfire)

146
00:10:57,283 --> 00:10:59,036
Whaaat?

147
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:01,834
His name is Makoto Kyogoku.

148
00:11:01,917 --> 00:11:03,170
According to the advisor...

149
00:11:04,005 --> 00:11:08,180
he's the world's strongest
security system.

150
00:11:08,472 --> 00:11:10,852
Th-the world's strongest?

151
00:11:10,935 --> 00:11:13,482
Come on, you know her, don't you?

152
00:11:14,484 --> 00:11:17,991
The advisor's niece,
young miss Sonoko.

153
00:11:18,325 --> 00:11:21,456
Heh, this is her boyfriend, it seems.

154
00:11:21,539 --> 00:11:24,003
Her... boyfriend?

155
00:11:24,086 --> 00:11:29,807
Hmph. Well now,
isn't this interesting.

156
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:34,148
(heavy breathing)

157
00:11:38,156 --> 00:11:39,659
Oh my.
Ah...

158
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:44,043
Don't tell me you intend
to stay the night here in the museum?

159
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:46,089
Yes.

160
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:50,055
I'd like to commit the dimensions
of this room to memory.

161
00:11:51,266 --> 00:11:54,522
I have a sleeping bag, too...

162
00:11:54,731 --> 00:11:57,653
and I've brought along
a bit of food as well.

163
00:11:58,071 --> 00:11:59,574
Tell me, young man.

164
00:12:00,284 --> 00:12:02,580
Would you care to make
a wager with me?

165
00:12:03,164 --> 00:12:05,879
A... wager?

166
00:12:06,379 --> 00:12:07,381
Huh?

167
00:12:07,841 --> 00:12:11,431
Kyogoku-san and Kaito Kid
are going to face off?

168
00:12:12,141 --> 00:12:13,268
Really?

169
00:12:13,351 --> 00:12:15,397
That's right.

170
00:12:15,815 --> 00:12:20,825
Apparently Makoto-san pleaded
his case directly to Uncle Jirokichi.

171
00:12:21,659 --> 00:12:25,752
Seems my "Kid-sama" remark
really lit a fire under him.

172
00:12:26,210 --> 00:12:31,722
Two handsome guys, throwing sparks
over little old me...

173
00:12:31,972 --> 00:12:33,768
it's just the best.

174
00:12:34,393 --> 00:12:36,147
"Over you," she says.

175
00:12:36,774 --> 00:12:40,322
It's not like Kid has
any interest in Sonoko.

176
00:12:41,032 --> 00:12:42,034
So?

177
00:12:42,117 --> 00:12:46,376
Which one do you want to win?
Kid or Kyogoku-san?

178
00:12:46,459 --> 00:12:51,094
Well, of course I want
Makoto-san to win, but...

179
00:12:51,678 --> 00:12:54,684
I don't really want
Kid-sama to lose, either.

180
00:12:54,768 --> 00:12:58,483
Huh? What's that supposed to mean?
Make up your mind.

181
00:12:58,776 --> 00:12:59,736
I mean, Makoto-san
is my precious darling, and...

182
00:12:59,736 --> 00:13:03,995
I mean, Makoto-san
is my precious darling, and...
(static)

183
00:13:03,995 --> 00:13:04,036
I mean, Makoto-san
is my precious darling, and...

184
00:13:04,495 --> 00:13:06,875
Hey, Sonoko?
The call's...

185
00:13:07,292 --> 00:13:09,881
Hello? Ran? Ran!

186
00:13:09,965 --> 00:13:11,217
(call disconnects)
Ah...

187
00:13:13,430 --> 00:13:15,893
No way, I've got no signal.

188
00:13:16,644 --> 00:13:19,400
A signal-jamming device.

189
00:13:19,818 --> 00:13:20,820
Ah...

190
00:13:28,126 --> 00:13:30,757
Good evening, young miss.

191
00:13:31,591 --> 00:13:33,929
K-Kaito Kid!

192
00:13:37,478 --> 00:13:39,775
H-how did you get in here?

193
00:13:40,484 --> 00:13:46,120
Oh, I just grew weary of flying
and stopped by to rest my wings.

194
00:13:46,955 --> 00:13:49,460
And while I'm here,
if I may...

195
00:13:50,670 --> 00:13:53,761
would you make a wager with me?

196
00:13:54,053 --> 00:13:58,144
A... a wager?

197
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,977
Kaito Kid came last night?

198
00:14:10,061 --> 00:14:11,563
To your room, Sonoko?

199
00:14:11,647 --> 00:14:13,526
That's right.

200
00:14:13,985 --> 00:14:17,993
He was just standing at the window,
like Peter Pan or something.

201
00:14:18,410 --> 00:14:22,627
Our guards spotted him,
so he beat it right away, though.

202
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:24,131
Didn't you hear about it?

203
00:14:24,214 --> 00:14:26,009
Of course I didn't.

204
00:14:26,093 --> 00:14:28,849
So? What did Kid come for?

205
00:14:28,932 --> 00:14:30,769
Heh, hehehe.

206
00:14:31,311 --> 00:14:36,405
Well, he asked me
to make a wager with him.

207
00:14:36,488 --> 00:14:42,542
As his reward for getting the gem,
he said he'd like to claim my lips.

208
00:14:43,169 --> 00:14:44,296
That's a lie.

209
00:14:44,671 --> 00:14:48,387
So? What did he really say?
Huh?

210
00:14:48,470 --> 00:14:51,643
Ah... well, the truth is...

211
00:14:51,978 --> 00:14:55,651
the alexandrite Uncle Jirokichi
is putting on public display...

212
00:14:55,736 --> 00:14:58,532
this time, the Green Emperor...

213
00:14:58,616 --> 00:15:01,580
if he manages to get
his hands on it successfully...

214
00:15:01,663 --> 00:15:04,962
he wants me to tell Uncle...

215
00:15:05,046 --> 00:15:08,427
that he'll trade the stolen gem
for a single item...

216
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:12,518
that he gets to choose,
from the Suzuki Group's art collection.

217
00:15:12,978 --> 00:15:15,483
What is it, this one item?

218
00:15:15,566 --> 00:15:19,032
Who knows? He said he'd tell us
after he stole the gem.

219
00:15:19,115 --> 00:15:21,453
So? What did you tell him?

220
00:15:21,536 --> 00:15:24,334
I yelled right back at him,
of course.

221
00:15:24,417 --> 00:15:27,382
Told him I wouldn't accept
a single condition...

222
00:15:27,465 --> 00:15:29,762
from a villain like him.

223
00:15:29,845 --> 00:15:32,100
Really?

224
00:15:32,183 --> 00:15:35,816
Well, I put it
a little more softly than that.

225
00:15:36,483 --> 00:15:40,658
Strange. What Kaito Kid targets...

226
00:15:40,742 --> 00:15:44,499
should only ever be the huge gems
called "Big Jewels."

227
00:15:45,042 --> 00:15:48,215
If the Suzuki Group really
had a gem like that...

228
00:15:48,299 --> 00:15:52,598
that advisor would've used it as bait
to lure Kid out ages ago.

229
00:15:53,392 --> 00:15:57,525
Besides, why tell something
that important to someone like Sonoko?

230
00:15:57,860 --> 00:16:02,368
Oh, so what about Kyogoku-san,
the one protecting the gem?

231
00:16:02,452 --> 00:16:04,372
Ah, Makoto-san...

232
00:16:05,458 --> 00:16:07,378
he's with the gem right now, too.

233
00:16:07,670 --> 00:16:13,474
R-right now? But that gem went
on public display starting today, right?

234
00:16:13,557 --> 00:16:17,357
Yes, at the Suzuki Grand Museum,
where we're headed now.

235
00:16:18,233 --> 00:16:22,700
Don't tell me he's standing next to
the display case with a scary look on his face?

236
00:16:22,785 --> 00:16:25,456
Well, you'll see when we get there.

237
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:32,387
(visitors murmuring)

238
00:16:38,315 --> 00:16:41,405
Huh? Why is he holding up
the gem like that...

239
00:16:41,488 --> 00:16:43,450
looking so bored?

240
00:16:44,536 --> 00:16:47,458
It's weird, isn't it?
It's fine, it's fine.

241
00:16:49,045 --> 00:16:51,299
See?
Y-yeah, sure enough...

242
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:53,053
Just like she said.

243
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:55,141
Well done, Sonoko.
Huh?

244
00:16:55,558 --> 00:16:59,023
To choose such a formidable warrior
for your suitor...

245
00:16:59,107 --> 00:17:00,986
that's my niece for you.

246
00:17:01,069 --> 00:17:02,447
Uncle Jirokichi.

247
00:17:02,990 --> 00:17:07,498
But Kid's predicted time is 10 p.m.,
after the visitors have left.

248
00:17:07,582 --> 00:17:10,004
There's no need to have him do that
this early...

249
00:17:10,087 --> 00:17:12,843
It's his own earnest request.
Huh?

250
00:17:12,926 --> 00:17:16,224
He wants to prevent any scheme...

251
00:17:16,308 --> 00:17:19,397
where Kid makes it look like
he stole it at the appointed time...

252
00:17:19,481 --> 00:17:21,861
when in fact it had already
been swapped for a fake.

253
00:17:22,278 --> 00:17:26,746
But even if he's a karate master,
he's still a high schooler, isn't he?

254
00:17:26,829 --> 00:17:29,877
Leaving him alone
to guard the gem...

255
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:32,507
Haven't you seen it?
Huh?

256
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:36,681
The eleven men
I sent to the Metropolitan Police...

257
00:17:36,766 --> 00:17:40,356
he mowed them all down with
lightning-fast, gale-force technique.

258
00:17:40,439 --> 00:17:42,903
That astonishing footage.

259
00:17:43,905 --> 00:17:49,332
But what if Kid pulls his trademark blackout
and plunges the place into darkness?

260
00:17:49,415 --> 00:17:51,253
No need to worry.

261
00:17:52,338 --> 00:17:56,263
He's the prince of kicks,
gifted with the mind's eye.

262
00:17:57,265 --> 00:18:01,147
If it goes dark, it's that scoundrel
who'll be in trouble.

263
00:18:02,358 --> 00:18:04,404
What's more...
Hm?

264
00:18:04,487 --> 00:18:07,243
I have a secret plan
of my own as well.

265
00:18:07,326 --> 00:18:08,913
A-a secret plan?

266
00:18:09,707 --> 00:18:13,881
Kid's specialty is his disguise art,
impersonating someone close to us...

267
00:18:13,965 --> 00:18:17,138
to slip right up to the gem.

268
00:18:17,889 --> 00:18:21,146
Yes, just as he once
disguised himself as my husband.

269
00:18:21,229 --> 00:18:23,025
I just fell for a fake phone call...

270
00:18:23,108 --> 00:18:24,569
that was all...
Hmph.

271
00:18:25,362 --> 00:18:30,331
Both the advisor and Inspector Nakamori
have had that experience as well, haven't you?

272
00:18:30,414 --> 00:18:33,420
Ah, that's why I keep doing this...

273
00:18:33,503 --> 00:18:35,591
pinching my cheek now and then.

274
00:18:35,674 --> 00:18:38,597
That may do just fine
for you gentlemen...

275
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:39,850
Ow, ow, ow!

276
00:18:39,933 --> 00:18:44,067
but doing something so crude
to a lady is hard to bring oneself to do.

277
00:18:46,279 --> 00:18:48,617
So what I've prepared instead...

278
00:18:49,577 --> 00:18:52,834
special-ordered from a Paris designer
and just delivered...

279
00:18:53,418 --> 00:18:58,679
is this dress, the only one
of its kind in the world.

280
00:18:58,763 --> 00:19:00,850
Oooh!

281
00:19:02,938 --> 00:19:08,031
B-but if Kid knocks you out
and strips a dress like that off you...

282
00:19:08,115 --> 00:19:10,327
That's only when it's a gentleman.

283
00:19:10,619 --> 00:19:14,377
As far as I know, Kid has never once
stripped a woman of her clothes...

284
00:19:14,460 --> 00:19:17,299
to impersonate her.

285
00:19:17,968 --> 00:19:20,264
In other words,
as long as I'm wearing this dress...

286
00:19:20,347 --> 00:19:23,603
it's plain at a glance
that I'm the real me.

287
00:19:23,687 --> 00:19:25,399
I... I see.

288
00:19:26,234 --> 00:19:27,988
Guess Sera doesn't count.

289
00:19:28,488 --> 00:19:32,873
Of course, I've prepared dresses
for Sonoko and her friends as well.

290
00:19:32,956 --> 00:19:34,918
Huh? M-me too?

291
00:19:35,002 --> 00:19:37,381
I only stopped by
on my way home from school.

292
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:40,262
Do change into it later, won't you.

293
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:44,645
After we've pinched
each other's cheeks, of course.

294
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:45,940
Yes.

295
00:19:46,024 --> 00:19:48,153
And also...
Ugh.

296
00:19:48,528 --> 00:19:52,119
Well, I'm sure the advisor wouldn't want
to send this Kid-killer boy...

297
00:19:52,203 --> 00:19:54,332
home either, would he?

298
00:19:55,167 --> 00:19:56,169
Heehee.

299
00:19:57,881 --> 00:19:59,802
Oh, that's right.

300
00:19:59,885 --> 00:20:04,352
When I checked the mailbox this morning,
there was a letter from Kid-sama inside.

301
00:20:04,435 --> 00:20:06,816
Huh?
What?

302
00:20:09,195 --> 00:20:11,699
It's addressed to Makoto-san.
Huh?

303
00:20:17,253 --> 00:20:21,344
What in the world does it say?
Ah...

304
00:20:22,638 --> 00:20:25,310
It's... blank.
Huh?

305
00:20:26,981 --> 00:20:30,404
Don't tell me he means he's calling off
this whole heist notice?

306
00:20:30,487 --> 00:20:34,662
That rogue, has he taken fright
at a karate master?

307
00:20:34,746 --> 00:20:37,418
I don't think it's blank.
Hm?

308
00:20:37,836 --> 00:20:40,173
Isn't this invisible ink?

309
00:20:40,257 --> 00:20:41,634
(sniffing)

310
00:20:41,719 --> 00:20:43,723
It's got a fruity smell to it.

311
00:20:44,808 --> 00:20:46,812
Ah...
Invisible ink?

312
00:20:46,896 --> 00:20:50,110
F-for now,
with my lighter...

313
00:20:54,452 --> 00:20:56,456
Ah, there's some writing!

314
00:20:58,585 --> 00:21:02,761
"Now then, let's have a fair contest.
Kaito Kid."

315
00:21:03,094 --> 00:21:05,057
Whaat? That's all?

316
00:21:05,140 --> 00:21:07,269
Yes. Nothing on the back, either.

317
00:21:08,021 --> 00:21:09,273
Heh, heh.

318
00:21:09,607 --> 00:21:12,696
It's probably some foolish taunt...

319
00:21:12,781 --> 00:21:14,492
along the lines of...

320
00:21:15,452 --> 00:21:18,166
"draw me out if you can."

321
00:21:18,751 --> 00:21:23,093
Now, Sonoko, Ran-chan,
let's go get changed.

322
00:21:23,176 --> 00:21:24,763
Ah... yes.

323
00:21:24,846 --> 00:21:28,520
Ah, um, before that...
Huh?

324
00:21:30,399 --> 00:21:31,986
Huh?
Ohh!

325
00:21:32,069 --> 00:21:33,990
Whaat?
Ah...

326
00:21:35,617 --> 00:21:39,000
Oooh!

327
00:21:39,667 --> 00:21:42,172
Ah, only once we're grown-ups.

328
00:21:42,589 --> 00:21:44,845
Good luck, Makoto-san.

329
00:21:44,928 --> 00:21:46,890
Ah... yes.

330
00:21:47,266 --> 00:21:48,351
I...

331
00:21:50,147 --> 00:21:51,691
I believe in you.

332
00:21:53,403 --> 00:21:55,950
Yes. I'll protect it to the end.

333
00:21:56,492 --> 00:21:58,246
I stake it on this fist.

334
00:22:00,793 --> 00:22:02,629
Come on, Sonoko.

335
00:22:04,467 --> 00:22:05,469
Yeah.

336
00:22:16,657 --> 00:22:19,956
I believe in you as well.

337
00:22:20,373 --> 00:22:23,839
That you'll keep
that promise of ours.

338
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:26,469
Yes.

339
00:22:28,849 --> 00:22:30,018
Of course.

340
00:22:31,521 --> 00:22:37,533
♪~

341
00:23:45,795 --> 00:23:51,055
~♪

342
00:23:51,138 --> 00:23:53,936
Kid! Kid! Kid!

343
00:23:56,357 --> 00:23:58,111
Wh-what is all this?

344
00:23:58,194 --> 00:24:00,657
Kid! Kid! Kid!

345
00:24:00,950 --> 00:24:04,581
Come on then, any time, Kaito Kid.

346
00:24:04,665 --> 00:24:08,172
Today's the day I'll show you
what's what.

347
00:24:08,757 --> 00:24:12,514
Hey, let me see that letter.
I won't take it out of the bag.

348
00:24:12,597 --> 00:24:14,936
H-hey, you...
Ha.

349
00:24:15,078 --> 00:24:16,578
Next Conan,

350
00:24:16,578 --> 00:24:20,778
"Thief Kid vs. Makoto Kyogoku (Part 2)".

351
00:24:36,278 --> 00:24:38,678
Next Conan's Hint:

352
00:24:38,678 --> 00:24:40,778
"Candle".

353
00:24:40,786 --> 00:24:42,331
Sonoko, whose side are you on?

354
00:24:42,415 --> 00:24:45,169
K-K-Ki...
The ultimate choice, huh.
